<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>HACKME Dashboard</title>
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.3.0/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
<body class="bg-dark text-light">
  <nav class="navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark bg-gradient bg-primary shadow mb-4">
    <div class="container-fluid">
      <a class="navbar-brand fw-bold fs-3" href="/">HACKME <span class="badge bg-danger ms-2">Vulnerable Demo</span></a>
      <button class="navbar-toggler" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#navbarNav" aria-controls="navbarNav" aria-expanded="false" aria-label="Toggle navigation">
        <span class="navbar-toggler-icon"></span>
      </button>
      <div class="collapse navbar-collapse" id="navbarNav">
        <ul class="navbar-nav ms-auto mb-2 mb-lg-0">
          <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/dashboard">Dashboard</a></li>
          <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/profile">Profile</a></li>
          <li class="nav-item"><a class="nav-link" href="/help">Help</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>
  <div class="container d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center" style="min-height:80vh;">
    <div class="card shadow-lg p-4 w-100" style="max-width:600px;">
      <h2 class="text-center text-primary mb-3">Welcome, <%- username %>!</h2>
      <div class="alert alert-warning mb-4">
        <b>Try these vulnerabilities:</b><br>
        <span class="badge bg-danger">IDOR</span> <a href="/account?id=1">View Account</a> (change id in URL)<br>
        <span class="badge bg-danger">CSRF</span> <a href="/transfer">Transfer</a><br>
        <span class="badge bg-danger">Open Redirect</span> <a href="/redirect?url=https://evil.com">Open Redirect</a><br>
        <span class="badge bg-danger">XSS</span> Try XSS in your username!
      </div>
      <div class="row g-3 mb-3">
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <a href="/profile" class="btn btn-outline-info w-100">Profile</a>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <a href="/change-password" class="btn btn-outline-warning w-100">Change Password</a>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <a href="/register" class="btn btn-outline-success w-100">Register</a>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
          <a href="/help" class="btn btn-outline-light w-100">Help</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <form class="text-center" method="POST" action="/logout">
        <button class="btn btn-danger mt-3 w-100" type="submit">Log Out</button>
      </form>
      <div class="alert alert-info mt-4">
        <b>Why is this vulnerable?</b><br>
        <ul class="mb-0">
          <li><b>IDOR:</b> Change the <code>id</code> in the URL to see other users' data.</li>
          <li><b>CSRF:</b> The transfer form has no CSRF protection.</li>
          <li><b>Open Redirect:</b> The redirect endpoint allows redirection to any URL.</li>
          <li><b>XSS:</b> Your username is displayed as HTML.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
